headline: Citigroup vs Wells Fargo: Which Wins on Dividends, Buybacks, Interest Rate Exposure?
summary: Wells Fargo (NYSE: WFC) and Citigroup (NYSE: C) both reported Q4 2025 earnings on January 14, 2026, yet investors sold off both stocks despite solid results. The selloff reflects concern over net interest income pressure in a higher-for-longer rate environment.
